name: Conceive
description:
A Yellow Garden Spider successfully mates and begins preparing a protective egg sac for the new brood. Intricate patterning stretches across the abdomen, making its tripled growth over the season more obvious. (Argiope aurantia)

2018. Nikon D60, 55-200mm Lens.

Photographed in situ, without the use of artificial lighting or staging. Photoshop only used for resizing.

1024x685 300dpi jpeg

Teia Beginnings Series: Part 1 - IV
